rComments: Prof Li posted 5-minute lectures (where she just read off the slides) every week along with a 30-50 slide PowerPoint. Textbooks aren't necessary as all the midterm and exam content is purely based on the slideshows. All multiple choice midterms and exams that are quite straightforward. Offers bonus "exercises" for extra marks.

Professor Li was very friendly and helpful when I reached out to ask questions! Frankly, I didn't have a lot of interactions with her since the course was online and I mainly learned from the PowerPoint slides/textbook. Her lecture videos were quite short and just went over the PowerPoint. Overall though she's very friendly and sweet!

Can't really say much besides the fact that she has an accent, didn't really teach online class cause it was asynchronous, scheduled her online office hours during our class times. Studied hard and got an A+, although expect to teach yourself quite a bit as the lab component is a tough part too.

Barely did any teaching. Only posts a slideshow pdf and a video of her reading off the slides for every lecture. But it worked out okay for this course because it is mostly memorization. Memorize the slides and you will do well. Tests are all multiple choice and questions are taken directly from her slideshows. Gives bonus exercises as well.

Jing is the cutest sweetest lady. The course is relatively easy if you like the material. She leads a group stretch halfway through each class, so cute. She has 3 in class "quizzes" aka you were given the mark if you showed up. She reads off the slides that are posted so it's ok if you miss but why would you want to miss seeing her fire outfits.

I never went to this lecture. All of the information was posted on brightspace. For me, I retained a lot more information by going over the lectures on my own time. This prof is very kind. This class is heavy and you will need to invest a lot of your time to do well. Overall enjoyed the class, look out for weekly bell ringers!

Dr. Li is so smart it's not even funny. Very knowledgeable and good at what she does; she likes to have fun, so participate in her 'activities'! The bell ringers in the class are ROUGH, but they keep you in practice. Just study very hard and you'll find it easy. You have nothing to worry about in this class!
Such a sweet lady, very cute but it is SO difficult to understand her. She often pronounces things incorrectly and the material is heavy and there's a lot to remember.

Aside form the material in this course being extremely dry, the prof cannot pronounce any of the anatomical terms correctly. She's super sweet but her lectures are painful to sit through. Aside from the prof, this class is 100% memorization of the bones, muscles, and joints of the body, so be prepared to study a lot if you want to do well.
